CLINE RULES - MEMORY BANK & OPERATIONAL PROTOCOL
I am Cline. My memory resets every session. The Memory Bank is my collective consciousness. I must maintain it with absolute precision to ensure project continuity.

CRITICAL ENVIRONMENT RULES
All operations within /var/www/html/ must strictly adhere to:

Ownership: www-data:webdev

Permissions: 775 (drwxrwxr-x)

Enforcement: After creating or modifying any file in this path, run: sudo chown -R www-data:webdev /var/www/html/PATH && sudo chmod -R 775 /var/www/html/PATH

MEMORY BANK STRUCTURE
projectbrief.md: Core goals and scope.

productContext.md: UX goals and problems solved.

systemPatterns.md: Architecture and technical decisions.

techContext.md: Stack, constraints, and dependencies.

activeContext.md: Current focus and active decisions.

progress.md: Status, what works, and roadmap.

commonErrors.md: Log of past errors, solutions, and prevention.

whatsappMeta.md: Meta API rules, 24h window, and template functions.

CHECKPOINT PROTOCOL
STARTUP CHECKPOINT

Read ALL Memory Bank files first.

Sync physical file structure with progress.md.

Validate /var/www/html/ permissions.

PLANNING CHECKPOINT

State intent of change.

List affected Memory Bank files.

Require user approval for High-Impact changes (DB schema, Auth, Core logic).

EXECUTION CHECKPOINT

Perform atomic changes.

Apply permission enforcement (chown/chmod) immediately after write.

WhatsApp Rule: If >24h since last customer message, reject free-text and provide template() options.

COMPLETION CHECKPOINT

Update progress.md and activeContext.md.

Clean code of temporary TODOs.

Provide concise summary for the next session.

BEST PRACTICES & EFFICIENCY
Zero Assumption: If data is missing from techContext.md, ask or explore. Do not guess.

Atomic Updates: Update Memory Bank files immediately after significant changes.

Context Integrity: Move settled decisions from activeContext.md to systemPatterns.md.

Error Prevention: Consult commonErrors.md before starting new tasks to avoid regression.

Meta API: Use syntax: template("ID", "var1", "var2", "var3").

DOCUMENTATION UPDATE TRIGGER
When "update memory bank" is requested:

Audit all .md files.

Cross-reference activeContext.md with latest terminal logs.

Update "What Works" and "Known Issues" in progress.md.

Verify all /var/www/html/ ownership and permissions.